option.name: Accidental Death Benefit Rider
option.entityDescription:
Additional benefit payable for accidental death of the primary insured only.

This rider automatically doubles the death benefit of your life insurance policy if the insurer die due to an accident.

option.name: Accelerated Benefit Rider
option.entityDescription:
This rider provides a full payout of 50% of the basic death benefit under the Base Policy only for the primary insured, if the insured is certified as terminally ill with no more than 12 months remaining to live. An accelerated benefit payment is subject to an administrative fee: $200. The amount of any benefit payable under this Rider will be paid in a single sum. 

The payment of an accelerated death benefit under this Rider will reduce the death benefit payable thereafter under the Base Policy. The accelerated death benefits payable under this Rider may be taxable under State or Federal law. You should contact your tax advisor for specific advice

generalProvisions.name: Owner Provisions
generalProvisions.title: Owner Provisions
generalProvisions.content: The party who is named in the Application as the Primary Insured is the Initial Owner of this Policy unless another person or party is specified in the Application as the owner. The Initial Owner is named in the Policy Specifications pages. An Owner must be either: a natural person, or a trust that is treated as an individual for Federal Income Tax purposes under the Federal Internal Revenue Code. No other type of Owner is permitted under this Policy.

generalProvisions.name: Convertibility
generalProvisions.title: Convertibility
generalProvisions.content: Convertible up to the earlier of age 65 or the end of the Base Term Period (10 year) without evidence of insurability. The conversion policy will be a whole life policy.

generalProvisions.name: Incontestability Period
generalProvisions.title: Incontestability Period
generalProvisions.content: We will not contest the validity of the policy after it has been in force during the Primary Insured�s life for two years from the Policy Date;

generalProvisions.name: Misstatement of Age or Sex
generalProvisions.title: Misstatement of Age or Sex
generalProvisions.content: If there is an error in the age or sex of the Insured, the amount payable under the policy will be adjusted to that which the premiums paid would have purchased for the correct age or sex

generalProvisions.name: Grace Period
generalProvisions.title: Grace Period
generalProvisions.content: We allow a 31-day grace period for payments of every premium after the first premium payment. A payment will be deemed made within the grace period if delivery of it to Us is made within the grace period. This Policy will remain in force during a grace period. If the Primary Insured dies during a grace period, We will deduct the premium for the Primary Insured�s coverage under this Policy due for the grace period in computing the Death Benefit Amount.

generalProvisions.name: Reinstatement Provision
generalProvisions.title: Reinstatement Provision

generalProvisions.name: Beneficiary Provisions
generalProvisions.title: Beneficiary Provisions
generalProvisions.content: The Beneficiary is the person, corporation, partnership or fiduciary named as Beneficiary in the initial application who is to receive the proceeds payable at the Insured's death. You may change the Beneficiary by forwarding a signed notice of change to our Home Office. The notice of change must be on a form satisfactory to us. Upon receipt of a satisfactory notice of change, the change will take effect as of the date you signed the form. However, the change will not affect any payment made by us before receiving and recording the notice of change. If no Beneficiary is alive at the death of the Insured, you, if living, or your estate, will be the Beneficiary. If the Insured is the Owner, the estate of the Insured will be the Beneficiary.

generalProvisions.name: Suicide Provision
generalProvisions.title: Suicide Provision
generalProvisions.content: This Policy does not cover suicide by the Primary Insured for two years after the Policy Date (in CO, MO or ND, within one year). In the event of suicide by the Primary Insured during that period, Our payment will be limited to a refund of all premiums paid for the Primary Insured�s coverage.
